HOUSE BILL No. 1258
_____
DIGEST OF HB 1258 (Updated February 19, 2026 4:11 pm - DI 106)
Citations Affected: IC 1-1; IC 2-8.2; IC 11-13; IC 16-27; IC 16-28;
IC 16-31; IC 25-1; IC 25-23.6; IC 27-10; IC 33-23; IC 35-31.5;
IC 35-33; IC 35-38; IC 35-40; IC 35-50; IC 36-1; IC 36-8.
Synopsis: Crimes of violence. Revises and consolidates the definition
of "crime of violence". Amends the definition of violent offender to
mean a person who is convicted of an offense or attempted offense that
is a crime of violence or a person who is charged with an offense or
attempted offense that is a crime of violence. Amends the definition of
"violent arrestee" to mean a person arrested for or charged with a crime
of violence that is a Level 1 felony, Level 2 felony, Level 3 felony,
Level 4 felony, or a Level 5 felony. Removes provisions concerning
repeat violent arrestees. Amends the definition of "violent criminal" to
mean a person convicted of a crime of violence. Adds: (1) dangerous
possession of a firearm with two priors; and (2) unlawful carrying of a
handgun with two priors; to the crimes of violence list. Makes a
technical correction and conforming changes.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Jeter, King, Carbaugh, Porter
(SENATE SPONSOR — FREEMAN)
