25 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3.4. (a) This section applies only to a violent
26 arrestee. or a repeat violent arrestee.
27 (b) The following definitions apply throughout this section:
28 (1) "Crime of violence" means an offense:
29 (A) described in IC 35-50-1-2(a); and
30 (B) that is a Level 1, Level 2, Level 3, Level 4, or Level 5
31 felony.
32 (2) "Repeat violent arrestee" means a person arrested for or
33 charged with a crime of violence who has a prior conviction for
34 a crime of violence.
35 (3) As used in this section, "violent arrestee" means a person
36 arrested for or charged with a crime of violence (as defined in
37 IC 35-31.5-2-79), that is a Level 1 felony, Level 2 felony, Level
38 3 felony, Level 4 felony, or Level 5 felony.
39 (c) A violent arrestee or a repeat violent arrestee may only be
40 released on bail set individually by the court following a hearing held
41 in open court. Before releasing a violent arrestee or a repeat violent
42 arrestee on bail the court must:
EH 1258—LS 6822/DI 151

25
1 (1) review the probable cause affidavit or arrest warrant; and
2 (2) impose money bail payable by surety bond or cash deposit.
3 (d) In accordance with IC 27-10-2-4.5(g)(2), a charitable bail
4 organization may not pay money bail imposed under this section on
5 behalf of a violent arrestee. or a repeat violent arrestee.
